      <Description>Removed usage of CSM (MID and High) for this calibration for MY19 since for MY19 the CSM uses the TW8845 in place of the TW8336. Also, updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>false</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="MISCELLANEOUS CONTROL III (MISC3); Note as defined in the TW8836 data sheet: FUNCTION: FCS; DESCRIPTION: 1 = Force decoder output value determined by CCS, and  0 = Disable.  " Name="REGISTER_0x12F_BIT3" References="TECHWELL TW8836 Data Sheet" Usage="LOW,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU">
    <CalID>_Y7b3UCxxEeW8XK_nvVgh2w</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
      <Description>Removed usage of CSM (MID and High) for this calibration for MY19 since for MY19 the CSM uses the TW8845 in place of the TW8336. Also, updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>false</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="MISCELLANEOUS CONTROL III (MISC3); Note as defined in the TW8836 data sheet: FUNCTION: CCS; DESCRIPTION: When FCS is set high or video loss condition is detected when LCS is set high, one of two colors display can be selected. Also  1 = Blue color, and 0 =Black. " Name="REGISTER_0x12F_BIT1" References="TECHWELL TW8836 Data Sheet" Usage="LOW,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU">
    <CalID>_WPSFACxvEeW8XK_nvVgh2w</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
      <Description>Removed usage of CSM (MID and High) for this calibration for MY19 since for MY19 the CSM uses the TW8845 in place of the TW8336. Also, updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>false</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="CORING CONTROL REGISTER (CORING); Note as defined in the TW8836 data sheet: FUNCTION: CTCOR ; DESCRIPTION: These bits control the coring function for the CTI. It has internal step size of 2." Name="REGISTER_0x118_BITS_7_thru_6" References="TECHWELL TW8836 Data Sheet" Usage="LOW,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU">
    <CalID>_HaURUCxuEeW8XK_nvVgh2w</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
      <Description>Removed usage of CSM (MID and High) for this calibration for MY19 since for MY19 the CSM uses the TW8845 in place of the TW8336. Also, updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Integer>
      <Value>1</Value>
      <MinValue>0</MinValue>
      <MaxValue>3</MaxValue>
      <Resolution>1.0</Resolution>
    </Integer>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="SHARPNESS CONTROL REGISTER I (SHARPNESS); Note as defined in the TW8836 data sheet: FUNCTION: CTI ; DESCRIPTION: Color transient improvement level control. There are 4 enhancement levels with 0 being the lowest and 3 being the highest." Name="REGISTER_0x112_BITS_5_thru_4" References="TECHWELL TW8836 Data Sheet" Usage="LOW,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU">
    <CalID>_uTJ1ECxsEeW8XK_nvVgh2w</CalID>
