      <Description>Removed usage of CSM (MID and High) for this calibration for MY19 since for MY19 the CSM uses the TW8845 in place of the TW8336. Also, updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>false</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="SHARPNESS CONTROL REGISTER I (SHARPNESS); Note as defined in the TW8836 data sheet: FUNCTION: SHARP; DESCRIPTION: These bits control the amount of sharpness enhancement on the luminance signals. There are 16 levels of control with &#x2018;0&#x2019; having no effect on the output image and &#x2018;15&#x2019; being the strongest." Name="REGISTER_0x112_BITS_3_thru_0" References="TECHWELL TW8836 Data Sheet" Usage="LOW,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU">
    <CalID>_3Nz1MCxnEeW8XK_nvVgh2w</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
